<subSubSection pageId="12" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,1354,2027]" pageId="12">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,321,1354,1379]" pageId="12">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
In the group, 
<taxonomicName box="[483,607,1355,1378]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Dichotomius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="periotoi" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[483,607,1355,1378]" italics="true" pageId="12">D. periotoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[614,677,1354,1379]" pageId="12">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[614,677,1354,1379]" pageId="12" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
is separated of the other brachypterous species in the group by the following combined characters: dorsal surface shinny and usually with brown or blue reflections; cephalic carina taller than wide, with two tubercles at apex (
<figureCitation box="[650,717,1426,1451]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="12.[151,250,1231,1253]" captionTargetBox="[268,1307,198,1194]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[265,1321,193,1210]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURE 7. Dichotomius (Selenocopris) periotoi n. sp.: (A) male dorsal habitus; (B) female dorsal habitus; (C) dorsal view of male paramera; (D) lateral view of male paramera; (E) detail of the fine punctures of the anterior pronotal excavation. Scale bar = 5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/272006/files/figure.png" pageId="12">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
A); dorsal surface of head smooth (
<figureCitation box="[1113,1181,1426,1451]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="12.[151,250,1231,1253]" captionTargetBox="[268,1307,198,1194]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[265,1321,193,1210]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURE 7. Dichotomius (Selenocopris) periotoi n. sp.: (A) male dorsal habitus; (B) female dorsal habitus; (C) dorsal view of male paramera; (D) lateral view of male paramera; (E) detail of the fine punctures of the anterior pronotal excavation. Scale bar = 5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/272006/files/figure.png" pageId="12">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
A); surface of pronotal anterior excavation smooth, bearing few and sparse fine punctures (
<figureCitation box="[925,1004,1462,1487]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="12.[151,250,1231,1253]" captionTargetBox="[268,1307,198,1194]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[265,1321,193,1210]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURE 7. Dichotomius (Selenocopris) periotoi n. sp.: (A) male dorsal habitus; (B) female dorsal habitus; (C) dorsal view of male paramera; (D) lateral view of male paramera; (E) detail of the fine punctures of the anterior pronotal excavation. Scale bar = 5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/272006/files/figure.png" pageId="12">Figs. 7</figureCitation>
A, E) and anterior portion of pronotal disc having two lobes.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
